ebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a normed space `F`, we have constructed in `PiTensorProduct.liftEquiv` the canonical\nlinear equivalence between `ContinuousMultilinearMap 𝕜 E F` and `(⨂[𝕜] i, Eᵢ) →L[𝕜] F`\n(induced by `PiTensorProduct.lift`). Here we give the upgrade of this equivalence to\nan isometric linear equivalence; in particular, it is a continuous linear equivalence.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/PiTensorProduct/InjectiveSeminorm.html#PiTensorProduct.liftIsometry","kind":"def","line":267,"name":"PiTensorProduct.liftIsometry","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/PiTensorProduct/InjectiveSeminorm.lean#L267-L281"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/PiTensorProduct/InjectiveSeminorm.html#PiTensorProduct.liftEquiv_apply\"><span class=\"name\">PiTensorProduct</span>.<span class=\"name\">liftEquiv_apply</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> uι}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Defs.html#Fintype\">Fintype</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u𝕜)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span